properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 4:18AM PST until March 2 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Las Vegas NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Owens Valley.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 6 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Strong crosswinds will create hazardous driving conditions
especially for high profile vehicles traveling along Highway
395.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will likely decrease overnight but a
surge of north winds behind a cold front will spread south
through the Owens Valley Sunday afternoon and Sunday night.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 6 AM PST MONDAY
